
# What is deluser ?
deluser command in Linux system is used to delete a user account and related files. This command basically modifies the system account files, deleting all the entries which refer to the username LOGIN.

deluser <username>  # to delete a user account

{Example}
kaushal@kaushal:~$ sudo deluser bhola
Removing user `bhola' ...
Warning: group `bhola' has no more members.
Done.